title: [North Barrow, Vestibule]
description: Heavy walls of rough-cut limestone blocks surround the low, dark vestibule, their surfaces etched deeply by thousands of years of seeping water, creeping lichen, and time.  A huge slab of granite, now broken and fallen away from the entry it once sealed, lies at the exit to the moors outside, and a narrow passage leads into a larger chamber to the north.
